info.description:
utilities is a super-awesome module which lets you perform basic image-processing operations at your finger tip. You can use it like this:

import utilities as ut
import cv2

#Load the image
img = cv2.imread('hf.png');

#Here we start using the utilities module.

#Use the translate function of utilities module. Returns a translated image.
translate_img = ut.translate(img, 50, 50);

#Use the rotation function of utilities module. Returns a rotate image.
rotate_img = ut.rotate(img, img.shape[0]/2.0, img.shape[1]/2.0, 45, 1.0);

#Display the images.
cv2.imshow('original', img);
cv2.imshow('translate_img', translate_img);
cv2.imshow('rotate_img', rotate_img);
cv2.waitKey(0);
cv2.destroyAllWindows();
